Decorating types with ContentPropertyAttribute allows shorter XAML syntax. As  has a ContentProperty attribute applied, this XAML is valid:

&lt;ContentView&gt;
  &lt;Label Text="Hello, Forms"\&gt;
&lt;/ContentView&gt;

This is equivalent to the following, more explicit XAML

&lt;ContentView&gt;
  &lt;ContentView.Content&gt;
    &lt;Label Text="Hello, Forms"\&gt;
  &lt;/ContentView.Content&gt;
&lt;/ContentView&gt;

